"OpenAPI 契约 MessageDto.status 枚举与实际实现不一致". The fix was supposed to u
pdate `docs/api-contracts/im.yaml` and regenerate the types. The YAML was update
d, but the generated types in BOTH `packages/shared-types` and `apps/mobile/lib/
models/generated/im/` were NOT regenerated. They still only have `sent` and `rea
d`.\n\nThis means the previous Blocking issue #2 is NOT fully fixed! The YAML wa
s updated but the generated code wasn\'t synchronized.\n\nThis is a Blocking iss
ue because:\n1. The previous review explicitly called this Blocking\n2. `make ch
eck-contract-sync` would fail\n3. AGENTS.md says "契约同步：packages/shared-type
s/ 是前后端的唯一真实来源"\n\nBut wait - the mobile code doesn\'t actually USE t
he generated models. It uses hand-written models (`apps/mobile/lib/data/models/m
essage.dart`). And the shared-types package exports the generated models but the
y\'re not directly used by the backend either. The backend uses `MessageResponse
Dto` class.\n\nHowever, the contract sync is still broken. If someone uses the g
enerated models, they would get type errors when receiving `sending`, `delivered
`, or `failed` statuses.\n\nActually, looking at the mobile generated model\'s `
decode` method:\n```dart\ncase r\'sent\': return MessageDtoStatusEnum.sent;\ncas
e r\'read\': return MessageDtoStatusEnum.read;\ndefault:\n  if (!allowNull) {\n 
  throw ArgumentError(\'Unknown enum value to decode: $data\');\n  }\n```\n\nIf 
`allowNull` is false and the status is `sending`, it throws an `ArgumentError`. 
